@startuml multi-tool-chain
title GigaChat multi-tool chain -- wire payload per round

actor       "User"                          as user
participant "UI / CoreAPI"                  as core
participant "Agent\nloop"                   as agent
participant "GigaChat\nadapter"             as adapter
participant "Local\ntools"                  as tools
participant "GigaChat\n/chat/completions"   as api

== How the loop works ==

note over agent, api
  Each **round** = one POST to /chat/completions, plus
  (if the response asks for it) one tool execution.

  **Continue** the loop while the response contains `function_call`
    (means: the model still wants a tool result before answering).

  **Exit** the loop the moment the response is plain `content`
    with **`function_call` absent** -- the model is done deciding,
    `content` is the final answer for the user.

  Rounds = (number of tool calls made by the model) + 1.
  Example below has 2 tool calls -> 3 rounds.
  Hard ceiling: HARNESS_MAX_ROUNDS (default 8).
end note

== Start ==

user -> core   : «Создай notes.txt и\nзапиши туда текущее время»
core -> agent  : handle(prompt, history=[])

== Round 1 -- no tool results yet, model must pick a first tool ==

agent -> adapter : chat(messages, tools=[now, file_write, ...])

note over adapter, api
  **HTTP request**:
    messages        : [system, user]
    functions[]     : [now, file_write, ...]
    function_call   : "auto"
    profanity_check : true
end note

adapter -> api   : POST /chat/completions
api --> adapter  : 200 OK

note left of api #FFE0B2
  **response  ->  CONTINUE loop**
    assistant.content       : ""
    assistant.function_call : { name: "now",
                                arguments: { "format": "human" } }
    functions_state_id      : "<X>"
end note

adapter --> agent : Message(tool_calls=[{name:"now", ...}])

agent -> tools    : execute("now", {format:"human"})
tools --> agent   : "2026-06-09 10:42:00 UTC"

agent -> agent    : history.append(\n   assistant(function_call=now, content=""),\n   function(name="now",\n            content="\"2026-06-09 10:42:00 UTC\"")\n)

== Round 2 -- model saw `now` result, now needs to act on it ==

agent -> adapter  : chat(messages, tools=[now, file_write, ...])

note over adapter, api
  **HTTP request**:
    messages         : [system, user,
                        assistant(function_call=now, content=""),
                        function(name="now",
                                 content="\"2026-06-09 10:42:00 UTC\"")]
    functions[]      : [now, file_write, ...]
end note

adapter -> api    : POST /chat/completions
api --> adapter   : 200 OK

note left of api #FFE0B2
  **response  ->  CONTINUE loop**
    assistant.function_call : { name: "file_write",
                                arguments: { "path": "notes.txt",
                                             "content": "2026-06-09 ..." } }
end note

adapter --> agent : Message(tool_calls=[{name:"file_write", ...}])

agent -> tools    : execute("file_write", {path, content})
tools --> agent   : "ok, wrote 26 chars to notes.txt"

agent -> agent    : history.append(\n   assistant(function_call=file_write),\n   function(name="file_write",\n            content="\"ok, wrote ...\"")\n)

== Round 3 -- model saw BOTH tool results, has everything it needs ==

agent -> adapter  : chat(messages, tools=[now, file_write, ...])

note over adapter, api
  **HTTP request** -- history now carries BOTH tool-call pairs:
    messages     : [system, user,
                    asst(fc=now),        function(now-result),
                    asst(fc=file_write), function(file_write-result)]
    functions[]  : [now, file_write, ...]
end note

adapter -> api    : POST /chat/completions
api --> adapter   : 200 OK

note left of api #A5D6A7
  **response  ->  EXIT loop**   (function_call is ABSENT)
    assistant.content       : "Готово, создал notes.txt с текущим
                              временем 2026-06-09 10:42:00 UTC."
    assistant.function_call : —
end note

adapter --> agent : Message(content="...", tool_calls=[])

== End ==

note right of agent #A5D6A7
  No function_call in response -> loop exits.
  Final content returned to caller.
end note

agent --> core    : final content
core --> user     : chat thread updated\n(SSE chunk + history append in state/chat.jsonl)

@enduml
